<!DOCTYPE section SYSTEM "mingle_help.dtd">
<chapter title="Apply tags to pages">
	<p>You can enhance management of your pages by tagging them. Tagging pages allows you to access any page you're looking for quickly and easily. </p>
	<section title="Tagging pages">
		<p>Tagging is available on the top of every page, just like <cref topic="creating_tags_for_cards_or_pages">tagging on cards</cref>. </p>
  		<steps>
  		  <item>To tag a page select "edit tags"</item>
  		  <item>Type in your tag or choose from the options available</item>
  		  <item>The page is now tagged</item>
  		  <p><screenshot alttext="tagging on wiki" src="resources/images/tag.png"/></p>
  		  </steps>
	</section>
<section title="Using tags to find pages">
	<steps>
	  <item>In the Mingle search field, type in the tag to find the page you're looking for. </item>
	  <p><screenshot alttext="using tag for search" src="resources/images/use_tag_for_search.png" /></p>
	  <item>Only pages and cards that have this tag will be returned as a result.</item>
		<p><screenshot alttext="search result" src="resources/images/find_page_tagged_with.png" /></p>
		</steps>
		</section>
</chapter>
